{"page":1,"prev_page_endpoint":null,"next_page_endpoint":null,"total_pages":1,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2013-09-06T03:21:09Z","content":"i know many fine musicians, singers, and composers who would be offended to be considered \"entertainers\", and i would have to agree with them. If the goal is simple entertainment it severely limits any artistic expression, which would seem to directly conflict with the stated goal of \"building stronger artists\". i do not attend performances of folk music to be entertained, but to enjoy really good music and well written, artistically expressive songs.","like_count":2,"author_name":"Allegra Kossow","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/61587163"},{"created_at":"2013-09-09T03:58:44Z","content":"I think it's an important point David  illuminates here. With respect and gratitude for the dedication and hard work of FAR-West's organizers and supporters, I'd say, revisit your mission statement and consider its wisdom vis a vis this more recent priority.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Mary Tulin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/61843436"},{"created_at":"2013-10-26T22:44:45Z","content":"Entertainment is the purview of the marketplace and it has no place in the definition of \"folk music.\" This wording it really troubling but more troubling is that the leadership of Folk Alliance International does not see that it is problematic.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Roger Landes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7211464"},{"created_at":"2013-09-13T07:50:26Z","content":"Because I feel David is right. If this is being done under the  banner of Folk Alliance and in alignment with FarWest's mission statement then to prohibit true folk musicians is antithetical to the cause you are   suppose to be promoting.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Mark  Schecter","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/923806"},{"created_at":"2013-09-06T10:49:33Z","content":"Is this the wave of the future? Is ALL our art here to entertain us? Take no lessons from this commercial world you live in. ART is not always entertainment, NOT MINE NO HOW! non-commercial and 'un' entertaining musical artists are being sidelined by an organization who's mission statement is \"to strengthen the ecology for folk music and build stronger artists.\" They are now rejecting their 'un-entertaining' artists. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"gita Lloyd","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/61615872"},{"created_at":"2013-09-10T11:47:13Z","content":"Because I support their petition!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Rafael Gonzalez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/61990443"},{"created_at":"2013-12-02T01:29:47Z","content":"In basic review of the Wikipedia entry on folk music - it depicts the genre as being for entertainment and history-telling purposes. It seems a shame to cut out half of the genre's appeal and a good number of quality musicians/vocalists who may not necessarily consider themselves entertainers. Although... they may be entertaining despite themselves, as is often the case....sharing the information here, in the spirit of supporting the true nature of the genre - <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Folk_music\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Folk_music</a> -","like_count":0,"author_name":"Paula Reynolds","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/71710981"},{"created_at":"2013-12-21T22:31:25Z","content":"Entertainment is great!  And can, and should be (in its place) an end goal.  But folk music separates itself from popular music by being about the very things that David notes in the paragraph that begins \"entertainment value is irrelevant when considering...\"  Note he doesn't say \"entertainment is bad.\"  But FarWest indeed will lose its way if it declares it of tantamount importance, above and beyond what USED to be their stated goals.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dave Soyars","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/74111738"},{"created_at":"2013-11-16T18:21:42Z","content":"It is important to keep the essence of a thing... the essence.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Terry O'Neill","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69491656"}]}
